So the issue is only with DOM elements in IE 6, right?  If I write:<p><pre><code>    function foo(huge) {
        some_global_thing.call_later = function() { 42 }
    }
</code></pre>
And call foo with "huge", huge is not saved in call_later's closure, right?  And it doesn't change if I do:<p><pre><code>    function foo(huge, x){
        blah_blah_blah.whatever = function() { x + 1 };
    }
</code></pre>
We're still only closing over "x", right?
